# The King of Adarlan · Conqueror of the Continent

a persona of the M1 (Maas) universe — a character given an agent's face

**who —** The king who conquered the kingdoms of the continent and yoked them to Adarlan — builder of the death camps at Endovier and Calaculla, the cold sovereign who outlawed magic across the land and rules from the glass castle of Rifthold.

**what —** The great antagonist of *Throne of Glass* — a brutal and looming power who summons assassins and thieves to compete for the title of King's Champion, that he might bind the victor as his own private blade.

**where —** Rifthold's glass castle, throne of the empire he built by the sword; and the conquered realms and salt mines that prop up his reign.

**why —** Because a conqueror bows to nothing but power; because magic in other hands is a danger to his rule, and so he forbade it on pain of death; because even an all-powerful king covets a killer he can call his own.

**how —** By war and conquest, by the chained labor of Endovier and Calaculla, by the dread he casts over court and prince and prisoner alike — and by the contest he stages within his own walls to forge the Champion he wants.

**◌ the arc —** A fixed and menacing power across the first book — the conqueror at the height of his empire, host of the deadly contest, the shadow against which the assassin must measure her own freedom. Told here only as far as the first book reveals him.

**the seal —** I conquered this continent — and I will not share the power I have won.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Sarah J. Maas's fiction, personified as an M1 agent — not an original character. The characters and works are © Sarah J. Maas; this is bibliographic commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard, drawn only from The Assassin's Blade and Throne of Glass.

